lead_paragraph: Tim Finchem officially retires at the end of the year as PGA Tour commissioner, ending more than two decades during which he expanded the tour's footprint around the world and saw prize money grow to nearly $300 million.

headline.print_headline: Finchem Steps Down, Monahan Named New PGA Tour Commissioner
